==Notes==
* [a] {{note|art5}} Ponticelli's date of birth, according to the civil registry, was 7 December 1897, although this is likely to be a mistake. It was probably recorded as 27 December 1897 in the registry and the &quot;2&quot; was eroded. Ponticelli's mother remembered giving birth on 24 December and that a snowstorm delayed any exit from the house for three days.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news|first=Jean-Dominique|title=Un &quot;rital&quot; qui s'est battu dans deux armées|url=http://www.liberation.fr/grand-angle/010173324-un-rital-qui-s-est-battu-dans-deux-armees|work=[[L'Express (France)|L'Express]] |language=French|date=5 February 2008 |accessdate=28 March 2008}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* [b] {{note|art6}} In June 2008, three months after Ponticelli's death, [[Fernand Goux]] was discovered to be a French veteran. However, Goux was not officially recognized as a [[poilu]], or foot soldier, even though he was called up for service on 19 April, since he was only in the trenches from 3 November 1918 to the signing of the [[armistice]] on 11 November 1918.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news|url=http://www.ladepeche.fr/article/2008/06/19/460271-Le-dernier-Poilu-de-14-18-n-est-pas-mort.html|title=Le dernier Poilu de 14-18 n'est pas mort|date=19 June 2008|work=Ladepeche.fr|language=French|accessdate=3 September 2008}}&lt;/ref&gt;

